sentences: Nicholle "Nikki" Jean Leary (born August 25, 1983) is an American singer-songwriter and occasional actress from St. Paul, Minnesota.
She first gained major recognition in 2008, when she was featured on Lupe Fiasco's single "Hip-Hop Saved My Life", from his second album The Cool.
In 2011, she signed as a recording contract with indie record label, S-Curve Records.
In 2011, she released the concept album, Pennies in a Jar.
In 2018, she signed a recording contract with Rhymesayers Entertainment for the release of her new EP.
